;; THE ANT PATTERNS IN A CONTROLLED VOCABULARY — overlay, not rewrite.
;;
;; Joe, 2026-07-16: "how about rewriting just the ant patterns in a controlled
;; vocabulary? (NNexus style as overlays if needed, or just hand-translation)".
;; Overlay. The prose is never touched — WR-2/I4 says a fast loop must not edit
;; its own constraints, and the .flexiarg files ARE the constraint. An operator
;; hand-translating would be fine (preferences are exogenous, that IS I4); an
;; agent quietly rewriting the library is the thing the ruling forbids. So the
;; text keeps its words and acquires annotations.
;;
;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
;; INDUCED FROM THE PROSE, NOT IMPOSED. Read the five THEN slots and the
;; vocabulary is already there, in the authors' own words:
;;
;;   white-space-scout : "raise G-adjustments for :forage, lower them for
;;                        :return and :pheromone, and stretch tau"
;;   cargo-return      : "apply negative G adjustments to :return ... slightly
;;                        boost :hold ... cap tau"
;;   pheromone-tuner   : "Bias :pheromone G downward ... anneal tau upward"
;;   hunger-coupling   : "hungrier ants lower tau, home safety lifts tau,
;;                        deficit reserves subtract from tau"
;;
;; Every prescription is (THING, DIRECTION). The things are the four macro
;; actions (policy.clj:12) plus tau. The directions are up or down. That is the
;; whole controlled vocabulary and nobody had to invent it.
;;
;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
;; WHY THIS INDEX IS NOT MY EARLIER PUN. oxf-claude-2 refuted
;; E-one-propagator-one-pattern.clj: flexiarg's 8 slots are `len(grammar
;; fields)`, while MetaCA's 8 is an EXPONENTIAL (N = Bool³, so index k IS
;; truth-table-3[k]). The slots have no structure for an order to be OF, and
;; precompEquiv + conjugacy prove the theory cannot supply it.
;;
;; N = the four macro actions is DIFFERENT IN EXACTLY THAT RESPECT: index k IS
;; action k. :forage is not "position 1", it is foraging. The index carries
;; content the way MetaCA's does and the way the slot list does not. That is not
;; yet a claim that it is an exponential (2² — see :open below); it is the
;; weaker, sufficient claim that the index is SEMANTIC, which is what makes FREE
;; name something rather than name whatever I happened to list fourth.
;;
;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
;; THE nu TEST — run FIRST, per oxf-claude-2, and it is the sharp finding here.
;; Their `settles_if_nu_has_fixed_point`: if nu has ANY fixed point p, the
;; constant colouring (fun _ => p) satisfies the constraint for EVERY shape map
;; s — so that nu settles instantly regardless of wiring, and settling is death.
;; The requirement is FIXED-POINT-FREENESS, not involution. (Caveat: that
;; theorem is not at the emitted sha ce6cc0c3c2 — I checked — so I am applying a
;; result I could not audit. Recorded in darktower-claims.edn.)
;;
;;   P = {:up :down}, nu = swap        -> forall d, swap(d) != d.  FIXED-POINT-FREE. ALIVE.
;;   P = {:up :down :unchanged}        -> swap(:unchanged) = :unchanged.  FIXED POINT. DEAD.
;;
;; THE NEUTRAL ELEMENT IS WHAT KILLS IT, and this is a real design constraint
;; discovered by a one-line test rather than by building the thing and watching
;; it settle. The obvious, comfortable vocabulary — "raise / lower / leave
;; alone" — is dead on arrival for every shape map. A three-valued direction
;; cannot host a propagator. `Bool.not` works for MetaCA for exactly this
;; reason: there is no neutral bit.
;;
;; The cost is real and must not be hidden: forcing P = {:up :down} makes each
;; pattern's prescription TOTAL over the actions — every action must be pushed
;; one way or the other. The prose does not do that (see :silent below). So the
;; vocabulary is not free; it demands a commitment the authors did not make.

{:vocab/id "ants-controlled-v0"
 :vocab/status :overlay-proposed          ; nothing adopted; no :by is filled
 :vocab/provenance "Joe + claude-6, 2026-07-16. Induced from futon3/library/ants/*.flexiarg THEN slots."

 ;; ---- the index set: SEMANTIC, unlike the flexiarg slot list ----
 :vocab/N
 {:source "futon2/src/ants/aif/policy.clj:12 — the four macro actions"
  :elements [:hold :forage :return :pheromone]
  :note "index k IS action k. This is the property the slot-list lacked."}

 ;; ---- the value set and its nu ----
 :vocab/P
 {:elements [:up :down]
  :nu :swap
  :fixed-point-free? true
  :rejected {:elements [:up :down :unchanged]
             :why "swap(:unchanged) = :unchanged is a fixed point, so by settles_if_nu_has_fixed_point the constant colouring solves it for EVERY s. Dead on arrival."}}

 ;; ---- the overlay: surface form -> canonical term. The text is untouched. ----
 :overlay/directions
 [{:surface "raise"                :maps-to :up   :in "white-space-scout THEN"}
  {:surface "boost"                :maps-to :up   :in "cargo-return THEN ('slightly boost :hold')"}
  {:surface "lifts"                :maps-to :up   :in "hunger-coupling THEN ('home safety lifts tau')"}
  {:surface "anneal ... upward"    :maps-to :up   :in "pheromone-tuner THEN"}
  {:surface "stretch"              :maps-to :up   :in "white-space-scout THEN ('stretch tau')"}
  {:surface "lower"                :maps-to :down :in "white-space-scout, hunger-coupling"}
  {:surface "negative G adjustments" :maps-to :down :in "cargo-return THEN"}
  {:surface "penalise"             :maps-to :down :in "pheromone-tuner THEN"}
  {:surface "bias ... downward"    :maps-to :down :in "pheromone-tuner THEN"}
  {:surface "subtract from"        :maps-to :down :in "hunger-coupling THEN ('deficit reserves subtract from tau')"}
  {:surface "cap"                  :maps-to :down :in "cargo-return THEN ('cap tau')"
   :caveat "STRAINED. 'cap' is a BOUND, not a direction — it does nothing until tau exceeds it. Mapping it to :down is the overlay flattening a conditional into a push. Flagged, not smoothed over."}]

 ;; ---- each pattern's THEN, as a partial function N -> P ----
 ;; PARTIAL is the honest word. See :silent.
 :patterns/then
 [{:id :white-space-scout
   :reading {:forage :up :return :down :pheromone :down}
   :silent [:hold]
   :verbatim "raise G-adjustments for :forage, lower them for :return and :pheromone, and stretch tau"}
  {:id :cargo-return-discipline
   :reading {:return :down :hold :up}
   :silent [:forage :pheromone]
   :verbatim "apply negative G adjustments to :return until a deposit event fires, slightly boost :hold when resting on the nest, and cap tau"}
  {:id :pheromone-trail-tuner
   :reading {:pheromone :down}
   :silent [:hold :forage :return]
   :verbatim "Bias :pheromone G downward when novelty is high and cargo low, but penalise it near the nest"
   :caveat "The prose gives :pheromone BOTH directions under different conditions ('downward when novelty high' vs 'penalise near the nest'). Read as :down here, which DISCARDS the conditional. See :the-real-obstruction."}
  {:id :hunger-precision-coupling
   :reading {}
   :silent [:hold :forage :return :pheromone]
   :verbatim "hungrier ants lower tau, home safety lifts tau, deficit reserves subtract from tau"
   :note "Touches NO action — it only moves tau. Under N = actions this pattern is EMPTY. That is a finding about N, not about the pattern: tau is a fifth thing the prose pushes, and it is not an action."}
  {:id :baseline-cyber-ant
   :reading {}
   :silent [:hold :forage :return :pheromone]
   :note "The identity. Its @aif-delta is literally {} and its THEN describes the loop rather than prescribing a push. Consistent with cascade-ants calling b0 FREE."}]

 ;; ---- what the exercise actually exposed ----
 :the-real-obstruction
 {:what "Every prescription in the corpus is CONDITIONAL, and P = {:up :down} cannot hold a condition."
  :evidence
  ["cargo-return: 'negative G to :return UNTIL A DEPOSIT EVENT FIRES' — a direction with a stopping condition"
   "cargo-return: 'boost :hold WHEN RESTING ON THE NEST'"
   "pheromone-tuner: ':pheromone downward WHEN NOVELTY HIGH AND CARGO LOW, but penalise it NEAR THE NEST' — opposite directions under different conditions, on ONE action"
   "white-space-scout: the whole pattern fires only when the `white?` detector holds"]
  :so-what
  "A pattern is not (action -> direction). It is (condition -> (action -> direction)).
   Which is EXACTLY oxf-claude-2's Q3 answer arriving from the other side: that is
   `rho : Sigma -> (Pat -> Pat)`, a sign-indexed family — the level-2 object, the
   same shape as switch(:boredom, sigma_A, sigma_B) and WR-4's :gate. The ants'
   patterns are not propagators. They are RHO, and their Sigma is the condition
   (:bored / :near-nest / :white / :cargo-stalled).
   So the ant vocabulary lands one level UP from where I was looking, and it lands
   exactly where the tower said it would. That is the first thing today that
   arrived where predicted instead of where convenient."
  :and-the-nu-test-still-bites
  "If Sigma is folded into the writer, N-patterns-as-arrows §1 says Sigma must be a
   MONOID, and nothing gives {:bored :near-nest :white} a multiplication. If it
   stays in the emission layer e : W(A) -> Sigma (which egoLambda FORCES — signs
   cannot ride the writer), no monoid is needed. The refuted lambda and this
   vocabulary point the same way."}

 :open
 [{:q "Is N = 4 actions an EXPONENTIAL (2^2), the way MetaCA's 8 = 2^3?"
   :note "Two binary features generating [:hold :forage :return :pheromone] would make the index determined rather than merely semantic, and FREE would name something forced. Candidates that do NOT obviously work: moves?/stays? and outbound?/homebound? — :pheromone is neither. I do not believe it yet."}
  {:q "Where does tau live?"
   :note "hunger-coupling pushes ONLY tau and so is empty under N = actions. Either N is actions + tau (5, not a power of 2), or tau is a different level — a precision on the choice rather than a choice. The second is more likely and would mean the ant patterns split into two carriers."}
  {:q "Is the totality cost acceptable?"
   :note "P = {:up :down} with no neutral forces every pattern to push every action. Four of five patterns are SILENT on some action. Filling those silences is authoring, not translating — it is exactly the operator decision the census must not make for itself."}]}
